parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of a collision can increase the risk of injury or fatality to the occupants.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates on the dashboard
the airbag does not deploy during a collision
the driver's side airbag does not deploy during a head-on collision.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of the airbag warning light can indicate a problem with the airbag system, which can lead to a failure to deploy in the event of a collision.

The failure of the ABS sensor can cause the ABS system to malfunction, leading to extended stopping distances, stiff brake pedals, and ABS light illumination, increasing the risk of accidents.
